{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-06-04T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Your average route to work might not resemble the one in today's image, but it shouldn't stop you from pedaling. World Bicycle Day invites us to rethink what's possible on two wheels—whether the ride cuts through city streets or remote terrain. Observed every June 3, the United Nations–backed day recognizes cycling as a practical way to move, supporting health, lowering emissions, and making mobility more accessible.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BardenasReales_EN-US9044910730_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BardenasReales_EN-US9044910730_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Where the road stops, the ride begins","Title":"Cyclist in Bardenas Reales Natural Park and Biosphere Reserve, Navarra, Spain","Copyright":"© Artur Debat/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.210213,-1.515728/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.210213,-1.515728;S9;Las Bardenas Reales, Navarra, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260603_BardenasReales\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Bicycle+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260603_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260603_BardenasReales"},"Ssd":"20260603","Name":"BardenasReales","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"9044910730","FullDateString":"Jun 3, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Cutting a surreal path through the high-altitude deserts of western China, Xitai Jinaier Lake (also known as West Taijinar Lake) is a striking salt lake in the remote Qaidam Basin. A stretch of National Highway 315 runs directly across its shallow waters, creating the illusion of a road floating between two worlds. On one side, the water often appears deep blue; on the other, a softer green hue, a contrast shaped by differing mineral concentrations in the brine.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Qinghai_EN-US8807254633_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Qinghai_EN-US8807254633_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Between the blues","Title":"Highway through Xitai Jinaier Lake, Qinghai Province, China","Copyright":"© Kaicheng Xu/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/35.668594,96.043144/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=35.668594,96.043144;S9;Qinghai Province, China&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260602_Qinghai\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Qaidam+Basin+China&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260602_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260602_Qinghai"},"Ssd":"20260602","Name":"Qinghai","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8807254633","FullDateString":"Jun 2, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every June, Pride Month bursts into cities and streets across the United States—but its origins lie in defiance, not festivity. The observance grew from the Stonewall uprising of June 1969, when LGBTQIA+ New Yorkers pushed back against routine police raids, igniting a movement that reshaped civil rights history.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.RockefellerPride_EN-US1087499810_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.RockefellerPride_EN-US1087499810_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Pride in plain sight","Title":"Rainbow flags at Rockefeller Center on June 28, 2020, New York City","Copyright":"© Noam Galai/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/40.758736,-73.978691/12?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=40.758736,-73.978691;S9;Rockefeller Center, New York&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260601_RockefellerPride\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Pride+Month+US&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260601_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260601_RockefellerPride"},"Ssd":"20260601","Name":"RockefellerPride","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1087499810","FullDateString":"Jun 1, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today is the last day of American Wetlands Month, but don't let that bog you down. Take today to shine a spotlight on wetlands. Held throughout May, this national observance shines a spotlight on wetlands—some of the most productive ecosystems in the United States—and few places show their power quite like Everglades National Park. From above, Florida's iconic wetlands unfold as a vast patchwork of shallow water, sawgrass, mangroves, and winding channels, shaped by freshwater slowly flowing south from Lake Okeechobee.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EvergladesWetlands_EN-US8572465847_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EvergladesWetlands_EN-US8572465847_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Follow the flow","Title":"Aerial view of Everglades National Park, Florida","Copyright":"© Tetra Images/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/25.286623,-80.898659/7?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=25.286623,-80.898659;S9;Everglades National Park, Florida&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260531_EvergladesWetlands\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=American+Wetlands+Month&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260531_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260531_EvergladesWetlands"},"Ssd":"20260531","Name":"EvergladesWetlands","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8572465847","FullDateString":"May 31, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Etosha National Park, Namibia, is not a place for soft starts, and the plains zebra foal in this image seems to get the memo. In a land this vast—nearly 8,600 square miles of salt pans and grassland—timing is everything, and hesitation is expensive. Lions, spotted hyenas, wild dogs, cheetahs, and leopards constantly pressure the herd—especially the youngest—so zebras are born ready. Minutes after arrival, they're upright. Hours later, they're moving.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-US8240577582_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.EquusQuagga_EN-US8240577582_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Reading between the lines","Title":"Plains zebra foal in Etosha National Park, Namibia","Copyright":"© Sharon Heald/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-18.98073,15.762634/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-18.98073,15.762634;S9;Etosha National Park, Namibia&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=plains+zebras&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260530_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260530_EquusQuagga"},"Ssd":"20260530","Name":"EquusQuagga","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"8240577582","FullDateString":"May 30, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal, Mount Everest rises into view, calm and unmoved as evening settles in. But on May 29, 1953, that stillness was broken. After years of planning and weeks of climbing, New Zealander Edmund Hillary and Sherpa mountaineer Tenzing Norgay reached the summit. At over 29,000 feet above sea level, they became the first people known to have stood at Earth's highest point.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-US0552794971_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SummitEverest_EN-US0552794971_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A 'peak' into history","Title":"Mount Everest summit, Sagarmatha National Park, Nepal","Copyright":"© fotoVoyager/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/27.980471,86.880623/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=27.980471,86.880623;S9;Mount Everest, Sagarmatha National Park, Solukhumbu District, Nepal&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Mt+Everest+summit+1953&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260529_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260529_SummitEverest"},"Ssd":"20260529","Name":"SummitEverest","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0552794971","FullDateString":"May 29, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As night settles over Suwon, South Korea, the old city wall pictured here shows that function doesn't necessarily cancel out beauty—it can create it. Built between 1794 and 1796 under King Jeongjo of the Joseon Dynasty, Hwaseong Fortress was more than a barrier. It was policy in stone: a reform minded push for a leaner, better-run state, driven by practicality and a deeply personal motive. Jeongjo ordered its construction to honor his father while strengthening a kingdom that wanted smarter systems, not just thicker walls.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-US1012626869_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HwaesongFortress_EN-US1012626869_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Design meets discipline","Title":"Old city wall of Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, South Korea","Copyright":"© aomam/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/37.289031,127.014114/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=37.289031,127.014114;S9;Hwaseong Fortress, Suwon, Gyeonggi, South Korea&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=hwaseong+fortress+suwon&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260528_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260528_HwaesongFortress"},"Ssd":"20260528","Name":"HwaesongFortress","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1012626869","FullDateString":"May 28, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"From above, the lake's smooth surface contrasts sharply with the rugged ground surrounding it. Hnausapollur crater lake—also known as Bláhylur—lies in the heart of Fjallabak Nature Reserve, a remote area of Iceland's highlands shaped more by volcanic activity than by human settlement. The crater formed when magma met groundwater, triggering an explosion that carved out the circular basin visible today.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Hnausapollur_EN-US2080493040_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Hnausapollur_EN-US2080493040_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A splash of blue","Title":"Hnausapollur volcanic crater lake, Fjallabak Nature Reserve, Landmannalaugar, Iceland","Copyright":"© Juan Maria Coy Vergara/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/64.055313,-19.031654/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=64.055313,-19.031654;S9;Hnausapollur, Iceland&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260610_Hnausapollur\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Hnausapollur+Iceland&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260610_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260610_Hnausapollur"},"Ssd":"20260610","Name":"Hnausapollur","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2080493040","FullDateString":"Jun 10, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Vernazza is a small seaside town in Cinque Terre, in Italy's Liguria region. Built around the area's only natural harbor, it has long been tied to the sea. First recorded in 1080 as a fortified settlement and maritime base, it later became part of the Republic of Genoa's coastal defenses. To this day, the village preserves its past in the ruins of Doria Castle and the watchtowers overlooking the bay. At the water's edge stands the Church of Santa Margherita d'Antiochia, first mentioned in 1318 and expanded in later centuries, with a bell tower overlooking the port. Above the houses and narrow lanes, steep terraces support vineyards and olive groves, shaped by generations of stonework in a landscape protected within Cinque Terre National Park, part of a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Picture an aperitivo here: a glass of local white wine, the harbor in view, and Ligurian favorites like focaccia and basil pesto—basically a postcard you can taste.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.CTNPVernazza_EN-US1571456265_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.CTNPVernazza_EN-US1571456265_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Taste the sunset","Title":"Vernazza, Cinque Terre, Liguria, Italy","Copyright":"© Kelly Cheng/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/44.135512,9.681952/8?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=44.135512,9.681952;S9;Vernazza, Liguria, Italy&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260609_CTNPVernazza\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Vernazza+Cinque+Terre+Liguria+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260609_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260609_CTNPVernazza"},"Ssd":"20260609","Name":"CTNPVernazza","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1571456265","FullDateString":"Jun 9, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today is World Oceans Day, so follow the lead of a creature that goes wherever the water takes it. Want to spot a lion's mane jellyfish? Look in cold northern seas. Its bell is split into eight lobes, and beneath it hang long tentacles and oral arms. As it drifts with the current, stinging cells snare plankton and small fish. For humans, the sting can be painful. Reactions vary, and even a washed-up tentacle can still hurt. The rule is simple: admire it, then leave it alone. Some lion's manes in Arctic waters have bells more than 6 feet across, but most sightings are smaller animals near shore after storms or strong currents.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.Cyanea_EN-US1146473249_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.Cyanea_EN-US1146473249_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Drift with the current","Title":"Lion's mane jellyfish swimming in the ocean","Copyright":"© Alexander Semenov Images/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Though mostly water, the lion's mane jellyfish can reach 120 feet in length—surpassing even the blue whale.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260608_Cyanea\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Oceans+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260608_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260608_Cyanea"},"Ssd":"20260608","Name":"Cyanea","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"1146473249","FullDateString":"Jun 8, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Since opening its doors in 1976, the Atlanta Botanical Garden has proven that beauty can be organized. Beds are planned, labels are placed, and every plant has a job. 'To have a garden is not as easy as it seems; it is just as difficult as governing a kingdom.' Nobel Prize-winning German author Hermann Hesse had a point.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GardenAtlanta_EN-US2319128074_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GardenAtlanta_EN-US2319128074_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":false},"Headline":"Plant your kingdom","Title":"Atlanta Botanical Garden, Atlanta, Georgia","Copyright":"© Marcus E Jones/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"Originating in ancient Persia, 'paradise' meant a walled garden, a meaning carried through Greek 'paradeisos' to Latin 'paradisus.'","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260607_GardenAtlanta\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=National+Garden+Week&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260607_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260607_GardenAtlanta"},"Ssd":"20260607","Name":"GardenAtlanta","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"2319128074","FullDateString":"Jun 7, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If your screen time has been winning lately, today is a good time to change that—we suggest hiking. National Trails Day, created in 1993 by the American Hiking Society, nudges people toward exploring trails.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.HikingNatchez_EN-US0663065299_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.HikingNatchez_EN-US0663065299_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Wander often, wonder more","Title":"Natchez Trace Parkway, Tupelo, Mississippi, USA","Copyright":"© The best photo is earned/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/31.54333,-91.38306/6?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=31.54333,-91.38306;S9;Natchez Trace Parkway, Tupelo, Mississippi&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260606_HikingNatchez\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=National+Trails+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260606_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260606_HikingNatchez"},"Ssd":"20260606","Name":"HikingNatchez","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"0663065299","FullDateString":"Jun 6, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"If nature had a 'do not disturb' sign, it would hang over Sarek National Park, often called 'the last European wilderness.' On World Environment Day, this remote corner of Swedish Lapland reminds us what the planet looks like when humans take a step back—and let the wild take the lead.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WedLapland_EN-US9813120088_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WedLapland_EN-US9813120088_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The quiet power of an unclaimed world","Title":"View from Skierffe Mountain over the Rapadalen river delta, Sarek National Park, Laponia, Lapland, Sweden","Copyright":"© Robert Haasmann/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/67.28834,17.66914/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-US&od=2&shading=flat&pp=67.28834,17.66914;S9;Sarek National Park, Laponia, Lapland, Sweden&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260605_WedLapland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Environment+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260605_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260605_WedLapland"},"Ssd":"20260605","Name":"WedLapland","Market":"EN-US","Hash":"9813120088","FullDateString":"Jun 5, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Poetic name, poetic appearance. Meet the snowy egret, whose all-white plumage and bright yellow 'slippers' on black legs give it a striking look. Once nearly wiped out by demand for its delicate breeding-season feathers—soft, lacy plumes prized for fashionable hats—conservation efforts saved its plumage.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PreeningEgret_EN-US9350488148_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PreeningEgret_EN-US9350488148_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Fancy feathers","Title":"Snowy 